    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="673"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/8–3048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dairen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-30T09:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 30, 1948—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 30—11:40 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Again called on Soviet ConGen re messages via Moscow after receipt Deptel
                    51, August 26 (received after sending Contel 32 to Nanking, repeated Department
                    127, Shanghai 50, Moscow 27). Soviets refuse commit selves but promise inform
                    Consulate in few days.</p>
                <p>Matters left basis current telegrams go Vladivostok and also may go Moscow.
                    Perhaps best if Moscow Embassy itself reports if Dairen telegrams suddenly
                    received by a new route.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 131, Moscow 29, Department pass Moscow, Nanking 35, Shanghai
                    54.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
